        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 12:13AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1213 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from near Raiford to 6 miles southeast of Scipio to 4
miles southwest of Wardville. Movement was east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arpelar...                        Gowen...
Mcalester...                      Canadian...
Pittsburg...                      Raiford...
Whitefield...                     Haywood...
Vivian...                         Porum...
Hartshorne...                     Haileyville...
Featherston...                    Krebs...
Lake Eufaula State Park...        Alderson...
Ashland...                        Indianola...
Crowder...                        Briartown...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
southeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
